 which would require him to resign his seat. The 10th district isn=E2=80=99=
t particularly competitive either=E2=80=94McCaul won his last election by n=
early 30 points=E2=80=94but Democrat <strong>Mike Siegel </strong>came
within five points of unseating him in 2018, during the last Democratic wav=
e. (The district was redrawn afterward.)<br/><br/>These vacancies serve as =
a reminder that when every single vote counts, the pressure falls to the wh=
ips. Right now, House Majority Whip <strong>Tom Emmer </strong>and his Demo=
cratic counterpart, <strong>Katherine Clark</strong>, have two of the harde=
st jobs in American politics. There may be more focus on the Republican whi=
p counts, but Clark is tasked with disrupting
